Louise Morlot

Bio

I am a PhD student in the Mailand lab at the Center for Protein Research at the University of Copenhagen. I am part of the Copenhagen Bioscience PhD Programme, a four-year PhD programme funded by the Novo Nordisk Foundation. I am interested in understanding mechanisms of cellular stress responses and exploring pathways involved in maintaining genome integrity. During my PhD I aim to develop targeted approaches combining cell biology and high resolution omics technologies to study DNA repair mechanisms and the consequences of DNA damages.

Education

M.Sc. in Biotechnology | September 2019 - September 2021

University of Strasbourg | Strasbourg, France

B.Sc. in Biology & Microbiology | September 2016 - May 2019

The University of Lorraine | Nancy, France

Experience

Research engineer | Developing single-cell approaches in the study of malaria parasite’s oocysts | Oliver Billker laboratory | MIMS Umeå university | September 2021 - August 2022

Master thesis | Oliver Billker laboratory | MIMS Umeå university | Feb 2021 - August 2021
